quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  95,1,"By the fig and the olive;",footnotes:182770:1
  95,2,"and by the Mount Sinai,",footnotes:182031:1
  95,3,"and by this city (of Makkah), a haven of peace:"
  95,4,"surely We created man in the best mould;",footnotes:182771:1
  95,5,"then We reverted him to the lowest of the low,",footnotes:182772:1
  95,6,"except those who have faith and do righteous deeds. Theirs is a never ending reward.",footnotes:182773:1
  95,7,"Who, then, can give the lie to you, (O Prophet), about the Reward and the Punishment?",footnotes:182774:1
  95,8,"Is not Allah the Greatest of all sovereigns?",footnotes:182775:1
  96,1,"Recite in the name of your Lord Who created,",footnotes:182776:1,footnotes:182777:2,footnotes:182778:3
  96,2,"created man from a clot of congealed blood.",footnotes:182779:1
  96,3,"Recite: and your Lord is Most Generous,"
  96,4,"Who taught by the pen,",footnotes:182780:1
  96,5,"taught man what he did not know.",footnotes:182781:1
  96,6,"Nay, surely man transgresses;",footnotes:182782:1
  96,7,"for he believes himself to be self-sufficient.",footnotes:182783:1
  96,8,"Surely to your Lord is your return.",footnotes:182784:1
  96,9,"Did you see him who forbids"
  96,10,"a servant (of Allah) when he prays?",footnotes:182785:1